1
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:43,159
Senior Sister, Senior Sister

2
00:00:44,159 --> 00:00:45,159
Fang Jie, you're back.

3
00:00:45,159 --> 00:00:45,640
Senior Sister.

4
00:00:46,399 --> 00:00:46,880
Fangfang.

5
00:00:47,679 --> 00:00:48,439
Senior Sister, Senior Sister.

6
00:00:48,679 --> 00:00:49,200
Senior Sister.

7
00:00:50,640 --> 00:00:51,079
Senior Sister.

8
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:52,719
Senior Sister.

9
00:01:22,159 --> 00:01:23,680
Working so hard as soon as you get back?

10
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,200
Not bad.

11
00:01:28,319 --> 00:01:29,120
You're already studying

12
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:30,719
the experiment plan for next semester.

13
00:01:33,439 --> 00:01:35,079
Getting ahead creates a virtuous cycle.

14
00:01:35,879 --> 00:01:36,799
No, but this plant of yours...

15
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:39,280
needs at least three more cultivations to show traits.

16
00:01:39,439 --> 00:01:41,040
You just need to record it after each harvest.

17
00:01:41,519 --> 00:01:42,760
No need to be this far ahead.

18
00:01:43,079 --> 00:01:45,079
Next semester's procurement list.

19
00:01:45,159 --> 00:01:46,719
Year-end safety inspection procedures.

20
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:49,640
Thirty-six snacks everyone loves. You...

21
00:01:50,239 --> 00:01:51,799
You're not planning to drop out, are you?

22
00:01:58,159 --> 00:01:58,879
You're dropping out?

23
00:02:05,079 --> 00:02:05,560
Gui Fang.

24
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:08,280
Our department has a quota for the direct Ph.D. program every year.

25
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:09,960
You'll be a senior next semester.

26
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:10,919
I intend to recommend you.

27
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,159
No need, Professor.

28
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,840
It would be a waste to give that spot to me.

29
00:02:16,919 --> 00:02:18,000
You're not doing research anymore?

30
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:25,319
Gui Fang, in farming practice...

31
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,240
you are the most talented student

32
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,599
I have seen in years.

33
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:34,800
I really don't need it.

34
00:02:37,039 --> 00:02:38,080
I might...

35
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,439
need to take a long leave.

36
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,639
Think it over.

37
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,000
Don't be in a hurry to refuse.

38
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:53,000
Doing it is what takes courage.

39
00:03:54,759 --> 00:03:56,639
Student Gui Fang found the difference.

40
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:57,599
Quite talented.

41
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:59,560
Gui Fang, can you teach me how to draw the rhizomes?

42
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:01,400
Your raw sketches are so beautiful.

43
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,120
The regrets of being in your twenties

44
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:05,319
can be fulfilled when you're nearly fifty.

45
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:06,520
I don't accept reconciliation.

46
00:04:06,599 --> 00:04:08,159
That's amazing.

47
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,199
Those researchers...

48
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:11,639
are exactly what I want to become.

49
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,840
That is the life I want to pursue.

50
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:38,639
Oh my god.

51
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:41,040
This still works.

52
00:04:41,439 --> 00:04:42,319
It's a pity to throw it away.

53
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,800
What? You want to pick it up and take it back?

54
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:46,720
Brother Xiao Can.

55
00:04:48,680 --> 00:04:49,160
Stop right there.

56
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,639
Let's not do that melodramatic romance drama stuff.

57
00:04:51,879 --> 00:04:53,439
I have no last wishes for you to inherit.

58
00:04:53,519 --> 00:04:55,399
And certainly no inheritance for you to distribute.

59
00:04:55,519 --> 00:04:56,839
I don't need you to be happy for me.

60
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,000
I have important family members...

61
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,600
but I don't need you to take care of them for me.

62
00:05:01,439 --> 00:05:01,800
Tian'er.

63
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:05,439
I hope you stay handsome and beautiful on your own.

64
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:25,639
Come on.

65
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:29,519
Buddy.

66
00:05:29,839 --> 00:05:30,240
Buddy.

67
00:05:30,959 --> 00:05:31,800
What about the computer?

68
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:33,519
Won't sell for much. I'll give it to you.

69
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,480
These shoes of yours are nice.

70
00:05:36,839 --> 00:05:37,600
Those are worth even less.

71
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,160
Take them all.

72
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:39,680
You haven't even used these toiletries.

73
00:05:39,879 --> 00:05:40,279
Take them.

74
00:05:40,759 --> 00:05:41,120
Take it all.

75
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,040
This curtain seems to suit me quite well.

76
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:44,560
Take it.

77
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,800
Use it as a tablecloth.

78
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,040
Or turn it into a skirt or something.

79
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:48,199
I'm a student.

80
00:05:48,399 --> 00:05:48,920
Give me free shipping.

81
00:05:49,199 --> 00:05:49,560
Sure.

82
00:05:49,959 --> 00:05:50,639
I'm a pampered wife.

83
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:51,600
Give it to me for free.

84
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,759
Brother Xiao Can, what about these clothes?

85
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,959
Just wear them as pajamas.

86
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:30,720
This was a gift for Sister Rui, right?

87
00:06:34,879 --> 00:06:35,680
What did you leave for her?

88
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,079
Nothing at all.

89
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,519
In her life from now on...

90
00:06:40,839 --> 00:06:42,079
it's best if there are no traces of me.

91
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:46,680
Buddy.

92
00:06:47,639 --> 00:06:48,160
How about...

93
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,600
we hold a living funeral for you?

94
00:06:53,199 --> 00:06:53,920
What's with you?

95
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,959
You think my mom and Xu Rui aren't sad enough?

96
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:01,560
Leave them alone.

97
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:03,000
Once is painful enough.

98
00:07:06,480 --> 00:07:07,519
Then... then...

99
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,360
Do you have any unfulfilled wishes?

100
00:07:13,360 --> 00:07:15,680
If I really have to think of one...

101
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:29,399
Xiaocan

102
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:30,879
Don't think about it

103
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,920
Why have a wedding when I'm dying?

104
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:34,319
Wouldn't that just burden someone for life?

105
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:35,759
No

106
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:37,560
I think it's been a perfect life

107
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,040
Brilliant

108
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:42,079
But if you insist on asking

109
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:43,759
There is one thing

110
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:44,319
Tell me

111
00:07:44,639 --> 00:07:45,360
I wish

112
00:07:45,519 --> 00:07:46,800
That my brilliant life

113
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:49,240
Would end in a dazzling display of fireworks

114
00:07:50,399 --> 00:07:51,439
Fireworks. Okay

115
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:52,480
I'll figure something out

116
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,000
If you force me to think of another

117
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:54,759
There is one more

118
00:07:54,879 --> 00:07:55,519
Tell me, tell me

119
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:56,480
I want to beat you up

120
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,040
A really solid one

121
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:00,319
You can only choose one

122
00:08:00,319 --> 00:08:01,079
Then I'll choose the second one

123
00:08:02,079 --> 00:08:03,240
Choosing one means

124
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,600
You can only choose the first one

125
00:08:12,879 --> 00:08:14,600
I didn't expect to leave tomorrow

126
00:08:14,959 --> 00:08:16,240
It's really quite emotional

127
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,160
Changed to tomorrow again?

128
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,519
Moved up? Wasn't it the day after tomorrow?

129
00:08:21,839 --> 00:08:22,519
Tomorrow

130
00:08:23,439 --> 00:08:24,000
Who said that?

131
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:25,079
The driver said so

132
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,360
Which driver?

133
00:08:27,399 --> 00:08:28,600
The truck driver

134
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,439
Who did you think I meant?

135
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,840
I thought you got a master to calculate it for me

136
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:35,960
You meant moving house?

137
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:37,799
What else?

138
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,399
I meant moving in

139
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,519
It's the same day

140
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,519
You scared me to death

141
00:08:46,279 --> 00:08:48,200
Auntie has lived here for over ten years

142
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,600
I didn't expect her to leave with just a few boxes

143
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,399
Didn't we rent a fully furnished place?

144
00:08:56,799 --> 00:08:58,039
Besides, that old furniture

145
00:08:58,159 --> 00:08:59,200
And old appliances can't be used either

146
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:00,799
Once my mom settles down

147
00:09:00,799 --> 00:09:02,320
We'll get new ones when she buys a new place

148
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,919
Do you feel that

149
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:06,519
Auntie has been unusually calm lately

150
00:09:07,879 --> 00:09:09,240
Indeed

151
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,919
Like when I suggested renting a place with a yard

152
00:09:12,399 --> 00:09:13,440
She signed without a word

153
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:15,679
I said to throw away all the old furniture

154
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:16,600
And she agreed

155
00:09:18,679 --> 00:09:19,200
Of course

156
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,360
We can't really empathize

157
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,519
After all, I've never lost a son

158
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:27,679
Don't worry

159
00:09:28,519 --> 00:09:29,840
I'll stay with Auntie for a few days

160
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:33,240
Just a few days?

161
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:35,679
And then? You'll forget me?

162
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:37,159
And throw yourself into someone else's arms?

163
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:39,840
No way, I can't bear to part with you

164
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:41,080
What else?

165
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:43,080
You want me to go with you?

166
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:44,639
Not go with me

167
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:45,480
But wait

168
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,559
I'll wait for you over there

169
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:48,960
Don't worry

170
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:50,279
With my social skills

171
00:09:50,279 --> 00:09:51,840
I'll definitely thrive over there

172
00:09:52,159 --> 00:09:53,240
When you get there

173
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:54,480
You'll find you feel at home

174
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:55,279
And brighten up the place

175
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:59,600
Then when I talk to my future husband

176
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,080
About my ex

177
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,720
I'll have to ask if he minds

178
00:10:03,759 --> 00:10:04,960
Future husband

179
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:06,360
Isn't that me?

180
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:20,919
Xiaocan

181
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,039
Then I'll wait for you two to come together

182
00:10:30,559 --> 00:10:31,919
I really don't want to go

183
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,440
I really can't bear to leave you

184
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,600
Fang'er, you made this soup base yourself, right?

185
00:10:42,159 --> 00:10:42,919
Smells so good.

186
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,039
Is it cooked?

187
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,039
It's cooked, it's cooked.

188
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:45,679
Eat this, have more of this.

189
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:46,240
It's definitely ready to eat.

190
00:10:46,240 --> 00:10:47,279
Don't boil this for too long.

191
00:10:47,559 --> 00:10:48,399
I'm not bragging to you guys.

192
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,279
But these duck intestines my Godmother makes...

193
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:51,360
Are the best in the world.

194
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,200
If she claims second place,

195
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:52,960
No one dares claim first.

196
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,679
Unlike our Xiao Yin.

197
00:10:55,360 --> 00:10:55,960
If she claims second place,

198
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,000
Then everyone else is first.

199
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:58,679
Li Wai.

200
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,240
If it's tasty, just eat more.

201
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:01,240
Godmother will...

202
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,559
Send you the secret recipe later.

203
00:11:02,759 --> 00:11:05,240
No way, every chef has their own touch.

204
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:06,919
I have to keep eating what Godmother makes.

205
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:09,919
Gui Fang.

206
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:12,679
You'll keep making this for us to eat, right?

207
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:18,120
Why are you kicking me?

208
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,120
What's wrong with kicking you?

209
00:11:20,759 --> 00:11:21,679
Come on, come on, let's eat.

210
00:11:21,919 --> 00:11:22,600
Eat more, have some meat, have some meat.

211
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,000
Have some meat.

212
00:11:23,279 --> 00:11:24,639
Here, have some greens, have some greens.

213
00:11:25,399 --> 00:11:25,960
Come on, come on.

214
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:27,919
Speaking of duck intestines...

215
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,440
In the dorm upstairs from us,

216
00:11:29,639 --> 00:11:30,759
There's a senior whose duck...

217
00:11:30,759 --> 00:11:32,240
Ate the experimental field of the class next door.

218
00:11:32,799 --> 00:11:34,720
Now the whole class is blocking the dorm door,

219
00:11:34,919 --> 00:11:36,200
Demanding the duck involved be handed over.

220
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,960
They want to kill the duck to vent their anger?

221
00:11:38,200 --> 00:11:38,879
No.

222
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:39,480
They...

223
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,720
Invited the duck involved to the lab.

224
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:45,080
Then the whole class is taking turns on guard duty,

225
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,519
Just staring at that duck,

226
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:47,840
Waiting for it to...

227
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:48,799
Poop the seeds out.

228
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:50,759
So they really want to vent feces.

229
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,000
We're eating here.

230
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:53,679
We're eating!

231
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,960
Why are you so disgusting?

232
00:11:54,960 --> 00:11:56,759
You guys mix fertilizer every day and still mind this?

233
00:11:57,279 --> 00:11:59,320
None of you actually like your major.

234
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:00,559
It's all for survival.

235
00:12:00,799 --> 00:12:01,320
Gui Fang...

236
00:12:02,039 --> 00:12:02,840
Don't you guys think...

237
00:12:03,279 --> 00:12:04,639
Gui Fang is like Mother Earth?

238
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,679
Loving life.

239
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,120
My foot...

240
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,120
Wei Mingtian.

241
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:12,039
Hungry, right?

242
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:13,799
Come on, eat more, eat more.

243
00:12:13,799 --> 00:12:15,200
Eat, have some meat.

244
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:15,720
Here.

245
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,039
Have some chicken heart.

246
00:12:17,279 --> 00:12:17,840
Grow some sense.

247
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,559
Speaking of chicken hearts...

248
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:21,399
Back in our hometown,

249
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:22,639
Before eating a chicken heart,

250
00:12:22,639 --> 00:12:24,360
You have to let someone take a bite first.

251
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:25,039
Why?

252
00:12:25,120 --> 00:12:25,639
Why?

253
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,720
Because if you eat too many solid chicken hearts,

254
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:29,159
You'll easily become hard-headed.

255
00:12:29,840 --> 00:12:30,639
You're really humorous.

256
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,720
Then if you eat a chicken heart that's half-bitten,

257
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,919
Wouldn't you become half-witted?

258
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:34,840
Never heard of that.

259
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:37,440
In my family,

260
00:12:37,759 --> 00:12:39,159
Chicken hearts are good stuff.

261
00:12:39,759 --> 00:12:40,720
Mom and Dad couldn't bear to eat them,

262
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,840
They saved them specially for the kids.

263
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,559
I anticipated your anticipation

264
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,960
Come on, brother. Sit here.

265
00:12:50,159 --> 00:12:50,639
Let's switch.

266
00:12:52,679 --> 00:12:53,039
Here, you sit.

267
00:12:53,279 --> 00:12:53,759
Here, eat up.

268
00:12:53,759 --> 00:12:54,440
Come on, eat more. You guys eat more.

269
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,240
Just eat, hurry.

270
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:56,080
Have some bean curd puffs.

271
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:57,399
Come on.

272
00:12:57,799 --> 00:12:58,399
Come on, eat up.

273
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,559
I beg you, just eat.

274
00:12:59,639 --> 00:13:00,399
This is my bowl, thanks.

275
00:13:00,840 --> 00:13:01,720
I want duck intestines.

276
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:02,960
Here, give it to me.

277
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:03,879
Here, Brother Li Wai.

278
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,639
There you go.

279
00:13:11,279 --> 00:13:12,120
Which side is the front?

280
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:13,519
Let me see.

281
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:15,519
Like this, like this, like this.

282
00:13:15,840 --> 00:13:17,039
Put this underneath first.

283
00:13:22,679 --> 00:13:24,279
It's not done yet. Take off your shoes.

284
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,360
Gui Fang, let me help you.

285
00:13:26,519 --> 00:13:27,279
Coming.

286
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:28,879
Fly!

287
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,440
I'm flying!

288
00:13:30,519 --> 00:13:31,080
Xiaocan.

289
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,399
Come on, Xiaocan.

290
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:33,519
Kong Xiaocan.

291
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:07,720
Stop it, stop it.

292
00:14:07,720 --> 00:14:08,360
Let's go wash up.

293
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,960
Alright, stop fighting. Go to sleep early.

294
00:14:10,159 --> 00:14:10,600
Brother.

295
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:12,000
Your second wish came true, didn't it?

296
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,600
You made this mess and just left it?

297
00:14:13,919 --> 00:14:15,039
You guys are unbelievable.

298
00:14:15,279 --> 00:14:16,759
No thanks, I'm on a diet.

299
00:14:16,759 --> 00:14:17,399
I'll drink plain water.

300
00:14:17,399 --> 00:14:18,759
Then I won't bother either. Let's go. I'm leaving.

301
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:19,519
Gui Fang.

302
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:24,159
You...

303
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:46,159
This is what I originally looked like.

304
00:14:54,679 --> 00:14:56,120
My mom can't accept that I did a Life exchange for her.

305
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,320
She will grow old.

306
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:58,559
The Life Energy will be useless.

307
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:05,000
It's okay.

308
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:07,399
Everyone grows old.

309
00:15:11,879 --> 00:15:13,000
The day your age was exposed...

310
00:15:14,399 --> 00:15:15,519
I happened to pull an all-nighter.

311
00:15:16,679 --> 00:15:17,720
I was feeling totally groggy.

312
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,000
As soon as I got home...

313
00:15:20,679 --> 00:15:21,960
I happened to run into a power outage.

314
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:24,399
Then I saw you shining a flashlight on your face.

315
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:25,879
Fixing the circuit breaker there.

316
00:15:28,799 --> 00:15:29,720
I thought I saw a ghost.

317
00:15:32,279 --> 00:15:33,360
I remember now.

318
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,639
I was wondering at the time...

319
00:15:35,639 --> 00:15:36,320
What was wrong with you.

320
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,080
The Mingtian Dam I told you about last time...

321
00:15:46,919 --> 00:15:47,600
Construction has already started.

322
00:15:48,559 --> 00:15:49,919
Your department's summer fieldwork this year...

323
00:15:50,639 --> 00:15:51,399
Is not far from my hometown.

324
00:15:52,159 --> 00:15:53,440
Do you want to stop by my hometown to have a look?

325
00:15:54,279 --> 00:15:55,039
My hometown...

326
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:56,919
Although it lacks water...

327
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:58,600
And there is loess everywhere...

328
00:15:59,519 --> 00:16:00,440
But when summer comes...

329
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,320
Many wildflowers grow from the soil.

330
00:16:02,919 --> 00:16:03,639
They are colorful.

331
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:05,799
Although I don't know their names...

332
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:07,279
They only exist in my hometown.

333
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,200
The sheep love eating them too.

334
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:12,879
There will be a chance.

335
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:13,919
Gui Fang.

336
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:19,600
You must come.

337
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:24,919
Go to sleep now.

338
00:16:26,919 --> 00:16:28,440
I know Brother Xiao Can is the apple of your eye.

339
00:16:28,919 --> 00:16:29,519
Now that he's gone...

340
00:16:29,919 --> 00:16:31,840
No one can fill the hole in your heart.

341
00:16:32,399 --> 00:16:33,039
But Gui Fang...

342
00:16:34,159 --> 00:16:35,480
You still have to live well.

343
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,039
You can't let the fifty years of life he gave...

344
00:16:38,759 --> 00:16:40,080
Only be exchanged for three years of your youth.

345
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:52,759
You're right.

346
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:55,960
I have to live well.

347
00:17:35,119 --> 00:17:36,480
Touch the hair, no fear. Touch the hair, no fear.

348
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:39,279
Buddy, aren't you playing ghost a bit too early?

349
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:42,480
Why sleep so much while alive?

350
00:17:43,079 --> 00:17:44,640
Death is an eternal sleep.

351
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,160
I want to look at you guys more.

352
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,640
You seem sick in the head.

353
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:49,000
I'm really done with you.

354
00:17:54,359 --> 00:17:54,759
Brother.

355
00:17:56,519 --> 00:17:57,319
After you croak...

356
00:17:58,319 --> 00:17:59,880
Don't you dare stand by my bed in the middle of the night.

357
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,279
Come look at tombstones with me.

358
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:10,559
Okay.

359
00:18:40,559 --> 00:18:41,200
Kong Xiaocan

360
00:18:41,759 --> 00:18:42,400
What time is it?

361
00:18:42,799 --> 00:18:43,559
Are you coming home or not?

362
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,039
Are you going to eat or not?

363
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:45,880
It's dinner time.

364
00:18:47,119 --> 00:18:48,319
Li Wai, come along too.

365
00:18:48,599 --> 00:18:49,680
Come eat at Auntie's house.

366
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:50,920
Thank you, Auntie.

367
00:18:51,079 --> 00:18:52,559
Don't call me Auntie. Call me Godmother.

368
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:54,359
Godmother.

369
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:56,440
Come on, come down.

370
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,519
Kong Xiaocan, why are your pants dirty again?

371
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,079
Slow down, slow down.

372
00:19:00,079 --> 00:19:01,039
Li Wai, run slower.

373
00:19:05,079 --> 00:19:05,640
Mom.

374
00:19:06,079 --> 00:19:07,319
I broke the vase.

375
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:10,240
Godmother, I broke the vase.

376
00:19:10,799 --> 00:19:11,559
I broke it.

377
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:12,880
I broke it.

378
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:13,839
It was me who broke it.

379
00:19:14,079 --> 00:19:15,160
It was me who broke it.

380
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,319
You've grown up.

381
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,039
You're taking responsibility.

382
00:19:18,599 --> 00:19:20,359
Does that mean we won't get a beating?

383
00:19:22,279 --> 00:19:23,200
What do you think?

384
00:19:23,599 --> 00:19:24,519
Haven't I told you?

385
00:19:24,960 --> 00:19:26,680
That the flower pots on the balcony are off-limits?

386
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:27,960
Li Wai didn't know.

387
00:19:27,960 --> 00:19:28,759
You didn't know?

388
00:19:29,079 --> 00:19:30,039
You used to be so obedient.

389
00:19:30,039 --> 00:19:31,559
Didn't Godmother say you couldn't?

390
00:19:32,599 --> 00:19:34,039
Kong Xiaocan led you astray, didn't he?

391
00:19:34,599 --> 00:19:35,759
Learning this stuff from Kong Xiaocan.

392
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,720
Brother, brother, don't be nervous.

393
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,000
Hold her favorite thing,

394
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:40,400
and say the words "I like you."

395
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,839
Don't be nervous. You got this.

396
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:42,720
No. Come on. Get ready.

397
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,039
Say it!

398
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:49,160
Say it.

399
00:19:55,279 --> 00:19:55,880
Happy Mid-Autumn Festival.

400
00:19:59,119 --> 00:20:00,160
He likes you.

401
00:20:31,559 --> 00:20:32,039
You're awake.

402
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:34,799
You're awake. Oh my god.

403
00:20:34,799 --> 00:20:35,799
You slept for quite a long time.

404
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:36,720
Where is everyone?

405
00:20:37,839 --> 00:20:38,400
Godmother and the others?

406
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:39,599
They went to tidy up the new house.

407
00:20:41,759 --> 00:20:42,279
Where did they go?

408
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,519
They went to tidy up the new house.

409
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,119
Where?

410
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,799
To tidy up the new house, grandpa.

411
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,119
How come your ears aren't working?

412
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:53,480
No.

413
00:20:54,640 --> 00:20:56,319
Look at the situation I'm in.

414
00:20:56,319 --> 00:20:58,039
My countdown is ticking.

415
00:20:58,039 --> 00:20:58,480
And they...

416
00:20:59,039 --> 00:20:59,839
are they in such a rush?

417
00:20:59,839 --> 00:21:00,599
Isn't it in a couple of days?

418
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:02,319
Alright.

419
00:21:02,319 --> 00:21:04,519
You're awake and know you're alive, that's enough.

420
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:05,759
I ordered takeout.

421
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,000
It'll be here in two hours.

422
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:08,880
Let's go check at the entrance.

423
00:21:13,119 --> 00:21:14,519
The takeout will be here in an hour.

424
00:21:14,519 --> 00:21:16,039
Let's go meet it. I'm hungry.

425
00:21:16,039 --> 00:21:17,160
What's the rush? I'm not hungry.

426
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:18,079
I haven't eaten yet.

427
00:21:18,079 --> 00:21:19,799
I'm hungry. Can you keep me company for a bite?

428
00:21:19,799 --> 00:21:21,079
I don't have time. I need to find my mom.

429
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,640
There's nothing in the new house right now.

430
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:23,839
There's nothing to eat there either.

431
00:21:23,839 --> 00:21:24,839
Let's grab a bite first.

432
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:26,160
No, there's no time left.

433
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,240
My time is running out.

434
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:28,880
I still have things to say to my mom.

435
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:29,359
Xiaocan.

436
00:21:30,039 --> 00:21:30,480
Here we go.

437
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:31,240
Yes, yes, yes.

438
00:21:31,319 --> 00:21:32,519
I prepared a eulogy for you.

439
00:21:32,920 --> 00:21:33,279
You...

440
00:21:33,759 --> 00:21:35,200
I originally wanted to read it at your funeral.

441
00:21:35,400 --> 00:21:36,279
But Li Wai was right.

442
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,960
Death leaves no time for goodbyes.

443
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,480
So since we have the chance now,

444
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,079
I thought I might as well read it to your face.

445
00:21:42,359 --> 00:21:44,200
That... that's really not nec— Listen up.

446
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:45,039
Kong Xiaocan.

447
00:21:46,079 --> 00:21:47,160
My best friend's son.

448
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:48,839
My boyfriend's childhood friend.

449
00:21:49,599 --> 00:21:51,160
Although I don't know him that well,

450
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,759
I know he is a good son.

451
00:21:54,359 --> 00:21:55,400
And a good buddy.

452
00:21:57,079 --> 00:21:59,160
I've also seen how he treats his girlfriend.

453
00:21:59,880 --> 00:22:00,400
I believe...

454
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:03,319
he could have been a good husband and father.

455
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:05,680
Especially when I learned...

456
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,160
that for his mother...

457
00:22:07,519 --> 00:22:09,440
he exchanged fifty years of Life Energy.

458
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:11,400
I was deeply moved.

459
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,000
I am a daughter.

460
00:22:14,519 --> 00:22:16,599
I can never be a son like him.

461
00:22:17,279 --> 00:22:18,799
But I really want...

462
00:22:18,799 --> 00:22:19,880
a son like him.

463
00:22:22,119 --> 00:22:22,599
Xiaocan.

464
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:24,960
We will never forget you.

465
00:22:26,519 --> 00:22:29,319
I hope my son can humbly learn from you.

466
00:22:30,119 --> 00:22:31,079
And willingly...

467
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:33,920
sacrifice himself for his mom.

468
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:34,960
Brother.

469
00:22:35,799 --> 00:22:37,279
These are words from the bottom of our hearts.

470
00:22:38,279 --> 00:22:39,119
Our dream...

471
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,079
is to have a son just like you.

472
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,319
I wish you two well.

473
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:48,359
Thanks.

474
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,279
My legacy...

475
00:22:51,039 --> 00:22:52,119
depends on you to carry it on.

476
00:22:53,119 --> 00:22:54,200
Your child...

477
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:55,599
has a part of me, too.

478
00:23:00,519 --> 00:23:01,799
Why does that sound so weird?

479
00:23:02,279 --> 00:23:02,759
What?

480
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:03,319
Brother.

481
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:10,119
You too...

482
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,960
I also wrote a eulogy for you. Listen to this.

483
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,880
On this day filled with grief and indignation,

484
00:23:18,319 --> 00:23:20,319
with hearts full of immense sorrow,

485
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:24,160
we attend the mournful memorial of Kong Xiaocan.

486
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:26,599
Today,

487
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:29,200
we mourn Kong Xiaocan together.

488
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,920
Because his life

489
00:23:31,359 --> 00:23:32,240
was glorious,

490
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:33,759
and even more so, industrious

491
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,559
and unpretentious.

492
00:23:36,799 --> 00:23:37,839
Hardworking,

493
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,480
helpful to others,

494
00:23:40,240 --> 00:23:41,319
kind-hearted,

495
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:43,400
and enduring hardship.

496
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,359
Kong Xiaocan's life

497
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,640
always shone with a spiritual light.

498
00:23:48,759 --> 00:23:49,200
However,

499
00:23:49,759 --> 00:23:51,200
Kong Xiaocan has left us.

500
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,279
But his spirit

501
00:23:53,920 --> 00:23:55,680
will influence us forever.

502
00:23:56,880 --> 00:23:57,920
Every generation.

503
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:00,200
Thank you.

504
00:24:01,599 --> 00:24:02,039
Quick, quick, quick.

505
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:05,359
Xiaocan.

506
00:24:05,359 --> 00:24:06,000
No, wait. Wait a second.

507
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,119
Why is it that just going home

508
00:24:07,119 --> 00:24:08,480
means I have to go through hoops?

509
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:09,599
No respect for elders.

510
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,480
By generation, you still have to call me Aunt Qi.

511
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:13,759
Listen to Aunt Qi...

512
00:24:13,759 --> 00:24:14,720
No time, no time, no time.

513
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:16,079
Brother, brother, brother.

514
00:24:16,119 --> 00:24:17,240
Xiaocan, someone had a crush on you.

515
00:24:22,079 --> 00:24:22,640
Who?

516
00:24:27,119 --> 00:24:27,640
Me.

517
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:36,799
Thanks.

518
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:38,559
And me.

519
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:44,519
Thanks to you too. Thanks.

520
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:45,680
Actually, it was me.

521
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:01,480
I don't mind.

522
00:25:04,279 --> 00:25:04,880
In fact,

523
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:06,599
I like you too.

524
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,640
Since it's rare for us all to be together,

525
00:25:12,039 --> 00:25:12,880
why don't we have a meal first?

526
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:13,880
You choose.

527
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:15,519
Which type do you actually like? Okay?

528
00:25:15,519 --> 00:25:16,160
Let's go, let's go, Xiaocan.

529
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:16,880
Let's go, let's go.

530
00:25:17,039 --> 00:25:17,640
Come on.

531
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,200
None of us are the same type.

532
00:25:19,279 --> 00:25:20,720
No rush. Let's eat.

533
00:25:21,079 --> 00:25:21,680
There's definitely something wrong.

534
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:22,640
Brother.

535
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:24,039
Can, Can, Can.

536
00:25:24,880 --> 00:25:25,480
Don't be in a rush.

537
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,640
Don't rush home.

538
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:27,920
You first...

539
00:25:27,920 --> 00:25:29,200
What are you doing? No, what are you guys doing?

540
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:30,000
What is going on?

541
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,400
No, brother, listen to me.

542
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,519
It's not that we won't let you go home.

543
00:25:33,039 --> 00:25:34,559
I've always had a question for you.

544
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:35,119
Ask.

545
00:25:35,559 --> 00:25:37,480
If one of your wishes could be granted right now,

546
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,000
what would you wish for most?

547
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:39,640
Not to die.

548
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:41,480
Let me ask you this way.

549
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:43,319
If we held a ceremony for you right now,

550
00:25:43,799 --> 00:25:46,480
what would you want it to be?

551
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:48,440
Don't think.

552
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:49,519
Don't think.

553
00:26:13,599 --> 00:26:14,200
Xiaocan.

554
00:26:25,279 --> 00:26:26,640
I should have known.

555
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,079
I told you,

556
00:26:28,079 --> 00:26:29,839
I don't want a living funeral.

557
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:30,880
I don't want a living funeral.

558
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,279
Why can't you just listen to me?

559
00:26:32,359 --> 00:26:33,279
I'm afraid of upsetting my mom.

560
00:26:33,279 --> 00:26:34,039
No, when she saw it...

561
00:26:35,319 --> 00:26:36,079
Did she get upset?

562
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:36,799
No, brother.

563
00:26:38,079 --> 00:26:38,519
Mom.

564
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:39,440
Mom.

565
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:39,880
Mom.

566
00:27:57,079 --> 00:27:57,920
Thank you, Auntie

567
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,119
We can hold the wedding

568
00:28:02,359 --> 00:28:03,000
but the certificate

